          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-09 14:45:05" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:μωρία&lt;SDBG:μωρία:000000&gt;} ‘foolishness,’ {D:32.57}) pertaining to thoughts devoid of understanding and therefore foolish</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>foolish</Gloss>
                <Gloss>nonsensical</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to be nonsense</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Some translators have endeavored to render μωρός[b] in the sense of 'nonsense´ as 'that which cannot be understood,´ but this could refer to some type of deep mystery. Accordingly, the expression 'what the world considered to be nonsense´ can often be better rendered as ‘what the world thinks makes no sense’ or ‘what so many people think is foolishness.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
